occurrenceRemarks: Plateau S of summit: 743m. 14°27.204' S, 48°26.606' W; at summit 760m.14°27.180'S, 48°26.583 W. Ascended ultramafic hill from southern end, collected plants from about halfway up (2887-2894), then from a plateau (above the 'Jesus Saude' sign formed from painted rocks) (2895-2901), then from the summit (2902-2909), then from a circut on N and NE sides within 20 m altitude of summit (2910-2929) and finally a few extras on the way down to the start (2930-2935). Delicate herb with almost leafless stems, and intense indigo-blue small flowerhead.FLORA DE SOLOS SERPENTINOS DO ESTADO DE GOIÁS.
locality: Southernmost ultramafic hill of Tocantins Complex, approx. 3 Km N of centre of Niquelandia; locations: halfway up hill from southern approach: 709 m, 14°27.275'S, 48°26.675'W;
